abbr.description: Defines an abbreviation or an acronym

acronym.description: Defines an acronym. Not supported in HTML5. Use <abbr> instead. Not supported in HTML5. Use <abbr> instead.

address.description: Defines contact information for the author/owner of a document

animate.description: The SVG <animate> element provides a way to animate an attribute of an element over time.

animateMotion.description: The SVG <animateMotion> element provides a way to define how an element moves along a motion path.

animateTransform.description: The animateTransform element animates a transformation attribute on its target element, thereby allowing animations to control translation, scaling, rotation, and/or skewing.

applet.description: Defines an embedded applet. Not supported in HTML5. Use <embed> or <object> instead.

area.description: Defines an area inside an image map

aside.description: Defines content aside from the page content

base.description: Specifies the base URL/target for all relative URLs in a document

basefont.description: Specifies a default color, size, and font for all text in a document. Not supported in HTML5. Use CSS instead.

bdi.description: Isolates a part of text that might be formatted in a different direction from other text outside it

big.description: Defines big text. Not supported in HTML5. Use CSS instead.

blockquote.description: Defines a section that is quoted from another source

canvas.description: Used to draw graphics, on the fly, via scripting (usually JavaScript)

center.description: Defines centered text. Not supported in HTML5. Use CSS instead.

circle.description: The <circle> SVG element is an SVG basic shape, used to draw circles based on a center point and a radius.

cite.description: Defines the title of a work

clipPath.description: The <clipPath> SVG element defines a clipping path, to be used by the clip-path property.

code.description: Defines a piece of computer code

col.description: Specifies column properties for each column within a <colgroup> element

colgroup.description: Specifies a group of one or more columns in a table for formatting

data.description: Adds a machine-readable translation of a given content

datalist.description: Specifies a list of pre-defined options for input controls

dd.description: Defines a description/value of a term in a description list

defs.description: The <defs> element is used to store graphical objects that will be used at a later time.

del.description: Defines text that has been deleted from a document

desc.description: The <desc> element provides an accessible, long-text description of any SVG container element or graphics element.

details.description: Defines additional details that the user can view or hide

dfn.description: Specifies a term that is going to be defined within the content

dialog.description: Defines a dialog box or window

dir.description: Defines a directory list. Not supported in HTML5. Use <ul> instead.

div.description: Defines a section in a document

dt.description: Defines a term/name in a description list

ellipse.description: The <ellipse> element is an SVG basic shape, used to create ellipses based on a center coordinate, and both their x and y radius.

embed.description: Defines a container for an external application

feBlend.description: The <feBlend> SVG filter primitive composes two objects together ruled by a certain blending mode.

feColorMatrix.description: The <feColorMatrix> SVG filter element changes colors based on a transformation matrix.

feComponentTransfer.description: The <feComponentTransfer> SVG filter primitive performs color-component-wise remapping of data for each pixel.

feComposite.description: The <feComposite> SVG filter primitive performs the combination of two input images pixel-wise in image space using one of the Porter-Duff compositing operations: over, in, atop, out, xor, lighter, or arithmetic.

feConvolveMatrix.description: The <feConvolveMatrix> SVG filter primitive applies a matrix convolution filter effect.

feDiffuseLighting.description: The <feDiffuseLighting> SVG filter primitive lights an image using the alpha channel as a bump map.

feDisplacementMap.description: The <feDisplacementMap> SVG filter primitive uses the pixel values from the image from in2 to spatially displace the image from in.

feDistantLight.description: The <feDistantLight> filter primitive defines a distant light source that can be used within a lighting filter primitive: <feDiffuseLighting> or <feSpecularLighting>.

feFlood.description: The <feFlood> SVG filter primitive fills the filter subregion with the color and opacity defined by flood-color and flood-opacity.

feFuncA.description: The <feFuncA> SVG filter primitive defines the transfer function for the alpha component of the input graphic of its parent <feComponentTransfer> element.

feFuncB.description: The <feFuncB> SVG filter primitive defines the transfer function for the blue component of the input graphic of its parent <feComponentTransfer> element.

feFuncG.description: The <feFuncG> SVG filter primitive defines the transfer function for the green component of the input graphic of its parent <feComponentTransfer> element.

feFuncR.description: The <feFuncR> SVG filter primitive defines the transfer function for the red component of the input graphic of its parent <feComponentTransfer> element.

feGaussianBlur.description: The <feGaussianBlur> SVG filter primitive blurs the input image by the amount specified in stdDeviation, which defines the bell-curve.

feImage.description: The <feImage> SVG filter primitive fetches image data from an external source and provides the pixel data as output (meaning if the external source is an SVG image, it is rasterized.)

feMerge.description: The <feMerge> SVG element allows filter effects to be applied concurrently instead of sequentially.

feMergeNode.description: The feMergeNode takes the result of another filter to be processed by its parent <feMerge>.

feMorphology.description: The <feMorphology> SVG filter primitive is used to erode or dilate the input image.

feOffset.description: The <feOffset> SVG filter primitive allows to offset the input image.

fePointLight.description: The <fePointLight> filter primitive defines a light source which allows to create a point light effect.

feSpecularLighting.description: The <feSpecularLighting> SVG filter primitive lights a source graphic using the alpha channel as a bump map.

feSpotLight.description: The <feSpotLight> SVG filter primitive defines a light source which allows to create a spotlight effect.

feTile.description: The <feTile> SVG filter primitive allows to fill a target rectangle with a repeated, tiled pattern of an input image.

feTurbulence.description: The <feTurbulence> SVG filter primitive creates an image using the Perlin turbulence function.

fieldset.description: Groups related elements in a form

figcaption.description: Defines a caption for a <figure> element

filter.description: The <filter> SVG element defines a custom filter effect by grouping atomic filter primitives.

font.description: Defines font, color, and size for text. Not supported in HTML5. Use CSS instead.

footer.description: Defines a footer for a document or section

foreignObject.description: The <foreignObject> SVG element includes elements from a different XML namespace.

form.description: Defines an HTML form for user input

frame.description: Defines a window (a frame) in a frameset. Not supported in HTML5.

frameset.description: Defines a set of frames. Not supported in HTML5.

g.description: The <g> SVG element is a container used to group other SVG elements.

header.description: Represents introductory content, typically a group of introductory or navigational aids

hgroup.description: Multi-level heading for a section of a document

hr.description: Defines a thematic change in the content

html.description: Defines the root of an HTML document

i.description: Defines a part of text in an alternate voice or mood

ins.description: Defines a text that has been inserted into a document

isindex.description: Put a text field in a page for querying the document.

keygen.description: Facilitate generation of key material, and submission of the public key as part of an HTML form

label.description: Defines a labelÂ for an <input> element

legend.description: Defines a caption for a <fieldset> element

line.description: The <line> element is an SVG basic shape used to create a line connecting two points.

linearGradient.description: The <linearGradient> element lets authors define linear gradients that can be applied to fill or stroke of graphical elements.

link.description: Defines the relationship between a document and an external resource (most used to link to style sheets)

listing.description: Renders text between the start and end tags without interpreting the HTML in between and using a monospaced font.

main.description: Specifies the main content of a document

marker.description: The <marker> element defines the graphic that is to be used for drawing arrowheads or polymarkers on a given <path>, <line>, <polyline> or <polygon> element.

marquee.description: Insert a scrolling area of text

mask.description: The <mask> element defines an alpha mask for compositing the current object into the background.

math.description: The top-level element in MathML is math

menu.description: Represents a group of commands that a user can perform or activate.

menuitem.description: Represents a command that a user is able to invoke through a popup menu.

meta.description: Defines metadata about an HTML document

metadata.description: The <metadata> SVG element adds metadata to SVG content.

meter.description: Defines a scalar measurement within a known range (a gauge)

mpath.description: The <mpath> sub-element for the <animateMotion> element provides the ability to reference an external <path> element as the definition of a motion path.

multicol.description: Experimental element designed to allow multi-column layouts

noembed.description: Non-standard way to provide alternative, or "fallback", content for browsers that do not support the <embed> element.

noframes.description: Defines an alternate content for users that do not support frames. Not supported in HTML5.

noscript.description: Defines an alternate content for users that do not support client-side scripts

object.description: Defines a container for an external application

optgroup.description: Defines a group of related options in a drop-down list

option.description: Defines an option in a drop-down list

output.description: Defines the result of a calculation

param.description: Defines a parameter for an object

path.description: The <path> SVG element is the generic element to define a shape.

pattern.description: The <pattern> element defines a graphics object which can be redrawn at repeated x- and y-coordinate intervals ("tiled") to cover an area.

picture.description: Defines a container for multiple image resources

plaintext.description: Renders everything following the start tag as raw text, ignoring any following HTML

polygon.description: The <polygon> element defines a closed shape consisting of a set of connected straight line segments.

polyline.description: The <polyline> SVG element is an SVG basic shape that creates straight lines connecting several points.

portal.description: Enables the embedding of another HTML page into the current one for the purposes of allowing smoother navigation into new pages.

progress.description: Represents the progress of a task

radialGradient.description: The <radialGradient> element lets authors define radial gradients that can be applied to fill or stroke of graphical elements.

rb.description: Delimit the base text component of a  <ruby> annotation

rect.description: The <rect> element is a basic SVG shape that draws rectangles, defined by their position, width, and height.

rp.description: Defines what to show in browsers that do not support ruby annotations

rt.description: Defines an explanation/pronunciation of characters (for East Asian typography)

rtc.description: Embraces semantic annotations of characters presented in a ruby of <rb> elements used inside of <ruby> element.

ruby.description: Defines a ruby annotation (for East Asian typography)

s.description: Defines text that is no longer correct

samp.description: Defines sample output from a computer program

section.description: Defines a section in a document

set.description: The SVG <set> element provides a simple means of just setting the value of an attribute for a specified duration.

shadow.description: An obsolete tool that was intended to be used as a shadow DOM insertion point.

slot.description: A placeholder inside a web component that you can fill with your own markup, which lets you create separate DOM trees and present them together.

source.description: Defines multiple media resources for media elements (<video> and <audio>)

spacer.description: Obsolete tool that allowed insertion of empty spaces on pages

span.description: Defines a section in a document

stop.description: The SVG <stop> element defines a color and its position to use on a gradient. This element is always a child of a <linearGradient> or <radialGradient> element.

strike.description: Defines strikethrough text. Not supported in HTML5. Use <del> or <s> instead.

style.description: Defines style information for a document

summary.description: Defines a visible heading for a <details> element

svg.description: Defines a container for SVG graphics

switch.description: The <switch> SVG element evaluates any requiredFeatures, requiredExtensions and systemLanguage attributes on its direct child elements in order, and then renders the first child where these attributes evaluate to true.

symbol.description: The <symbol> element is used to define graphical template objects which can be instantiated by a <use> element.

tbody.description: Groups the body content in a table

td.description: Defines a cell in a table

template.description: Defines a container for content that should be hidden when the page loads

text.description: The SVG <text> element draws a graphics element consisting of text.

textPath.description: To render text along the shape of a <path>, enclose the text in a <textPath> element that has an href attribute with a reference to the <path> element.

textarea.description: Defines a multiline input control (text area)

tfoot.description: Groups the footer content in a table

th.description: Defines a header cell in a table

thead.description: Groups the header content in a table

title.description: Defines a title for the document

tr.description: Defines a row in a table

track.description: Defines text tracks for media elements (<video> and <audio>)

tspan.description: The SVG <tspan> element defines a subtext within a <text> element or another <tspan> element.

tt.description: Defines teletype text. Not supported in HTML5. Use CSS instead.

u.description: Defines some text that is unarticulated and styled differently from normal text

use.description: The <use> element takes nodes from within the SVG document, and duplicates them somewhere else.

view.description: A view is a defined way to view the image, like a zoom level or a detail view.

xmp.description: Renders text between the start and end tags without interpreting the HTML in between and using a monospaced font.
